esearching, and publication, research-creation works to render daily life in the academy more pedagogically, politically, and affectively sustainable, as well as more responsive to issues of social and ecological justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aArtsxResearch. 0aArtsxStudy and teaching (Higher) 0aArtsxStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.) 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.). 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectives. 0aEducation, HigherxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEducation, HigherxSocial aspects. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478004646zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004646423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478004646.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles